<string id="informer_recipt1"><text>Eh, fine... You didn't confuse the number of zeros? Okay, here's your money, I hope it's worth it. Come on, upload the info.</text></string>
<string id="informer_recipt2"><text>Alright.</text></string>
<string id="alenka_info"><text>Don't shoot! Alyonka is waiting for me there... I have some information for you. I served as a clerk there, at our base: I was sitting at a computer, messing around with documents and reports. And then, when our guys started to rob your fellow stalkers, it became unbearable! It's disgusting... Well, okay, not about that now. I read one file there by accident... Well, not really by accident... Basically, I had to tinker a bit with the code... I didn’t copy the file itself, but I tried to remember as much as I could. There was a report by the eggheads about artifact changes in anomalies! I know, it sounds incredible! So this file said that if you take some kind of me... Meso-something called "Great-grandmother's beads" - a moronic name; I immediately remembered it, just don’t ask what it is, I can’t even imagine, and put it in "Whirlgig", then in ten minutes, I think another artifact will appear! Well, like it's still the same artifact, only it's properties will change. It radiates a field; everything that that flies into it  quickly slows down. I thought: “That means bullets!” It also stops the blood, like, you stop bleeding, improves health, but it irradiates the wearer. That's it. I hope this information helps you more than me... And it's worth sparing my life... Don’t kill me, Marked One, please...</text></string>
